      <section eId="sec_732">
        <num>732</num>
        <heading>Written warranty; contents</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_732__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The warrantor will, as a minimum remedy, make repairs or indemnify\nthe buyer for the actual cost of repairing any rust damage covered by\nthe warranty.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_732__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>The warrantor will honor all valid claims under the warranty\nregardless of their number.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_732__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Nothing contained in this section shall be deemed to preclude a\nwarrantor from entering into a contract requiring a financially solvent\napplicator to be initially responsible for the cost of any corrective\naction as a result of the negligence of the applicator of the\naftermarket rustproofing.\n  3. Length of warranty. This warranty shall be valid for a period of\nnot less than five years from the date of the application of the\naftermarket rustproofing, provided, however, that this section shall not\nbe construed as to extend this warranty to a person who is a subsequent\ntransferee of the buyer.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
